The paper discusses the development and analysis of machine learning approaches for detecting Android malware, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of Bayesian classification suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The study also involves empirical results and comparative analysis, indicating a potential focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) subcategories.
